"title": "5587: trade",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5587",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Fair business transactions are essential to distribute the benefits of God's goodness between individuals and nations. Scripture insists on honesty in trade and warns against abuses.</p>\n<h2>Trade in ancient Israel</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:14\">LEV 25:14</a> <em>Land transactions required the approval of the ruler of the state</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:7\">2KI 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:1\">2KI 7:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:31-Neh3:32\">NEH 3:31–3:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:13-Prov31:18\">PRO 31:13–31:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:24\">PRO 31:24</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:11\">ZEP 1:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:12\">MAT 21:12</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:15-Mark11:16\">MRK 11:15–11:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:45\">LUK 19:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:14-John2:16\">JHN 2:14–2:16</a> <em>trade in Jerusalem in Jesus Christ's day</em></p>\n<h2>International trade</h2>\n<h3>Under Solomon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:26-1Kgs9:28\">1KI 9:26–9:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr8:17-2Chr8:18\">2CH 8:17–8:18</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:14-1Kgs10:15\">1KI 10:14–10:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:13-2Chr9:14\">2CH 9:13–9:14</a> <em>Transit taxes were imposed on inter-state trade. Also some taxes were owed to the state by merchants for some kinds of trade</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:28-1Kgs10:29\">1KI 10:28–10:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:16-2Chr1:17\">2CH 1:16–1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:21\">2CH 9:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song3:6-Song3:7\">SNG 3:6–3:7</a></p>\n<h3>Under Jehoshaphat</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:48\">1KI 22:48</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:35-2Chr20:37\">2CH 20:35–20:37</a> <em>Soon afterwards the port of Ezion Geber passed back into the hands of Edom (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs8:20\">2Ki 8:20</a>).</em></p>\n<h3>In the Psalms</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:23\">PSA 107:23</a></p>\n<h2>Trade among the nations</h2>\n<h3>Hittites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:16\">GEN 23:16</a></p>\n<h3>Shechemites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:10\">GEN 34:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:21\">GEN 34:21</a></p>\n<h3>Ishmaelites</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:25\">GEN 37:25</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Midianites</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:28\">GEN 37:28</a></p>\n<h3>Egypt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:34\">GEN 42:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:14\">ISA 45:14</a></p>\n<h3>Sheba</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:19\">JOB 6:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:20\">JER 6:20</a></p>\n<h3>Damascus</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:34\">1KI 20:34</a></p>\n<h3>Tyre and the surrounding nations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:8\">ISA 23:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:1-Ezek27:36\">EZK 27:1–27:36</a></p>\n<h3>Tarshish</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:13\">EZK 38:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:3-Jonah1:5\">JON 1:3–1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Nineveh</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:16\">NAM 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>Ancient Babylon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:29\">EZK 16:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:4\">EZK 17:4</a></p>\n<h3>Babylon the Great</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:9-Rev18:24\">REV 18:9–18:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:2-Rev18:3\">REV 18:2–18:3</a></p>\n<h2>Honesty is essential in trade</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:35-Lev19:36\">LEV 19:35–19:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13-Deut25:16\">DEU 25:13–25:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:1\">PRO 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:11\">PRO 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:10\">PRO 20:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:23\">PRO 20:23</a></p>\n<h2>Warnings against abuses in trade</h2>\n<h3>Dishonesty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:4-Amos8:5\">AMO 8:4–8:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:18\">EZK 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:7\">HOS 12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:10-Mic6:11\">MIC 6:10–6:11</a></p>\n<h3>Oppression</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:18-Job20:19\">JOB 20:18–20:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:16\">EZK 28:16</a></p>\n<h3>Overconfidence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:13-Jas4:16\">JAS 4:13–4:16</a></p>\n<h3>Pride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:5\">EZK 28:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:12\">ISA 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:16\">ISA 2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:17-Isa23:18\">ISA 23:17–23:18</a></p>\n<h3>Sabbath trading</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:31\">NEH 10:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:15-Neh13:22\">NEH 13:15–13:22</a></p>\n<h3>The slave trade</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:26-Gen37:28\">GEN 37:26–37:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:36\">GEN 37:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:1\">GEN 39:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:6\">AMO 2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:6\">AMO 8:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:10\">1TI 1:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:13\">REV 18:13</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrilegious trade</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:14-John2:16\">JHN 2:14–2:16</a></p>\n<h3>Immoral trade</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:3\">JOL 3:3</a></p>\n<h2>The imagery of trade applied to spiritual matters</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:45-Matt13:46\">MAT 13:45–13:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:23\">PRO 23:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:14-Matt25:18\">MAT 25:14–25:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:13\">LUK 19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:20</a></p>",
